This framework was developed as a capstone synthesis of the
University of Central Florida Master of Arts in Instructional
Systems program. It operationalizes peer-reviewed instructional
design research into structured LLM-as-a-judge evaluation rubrics.

The LLM-as-a-judge evaluation pattern implemented by this framework
draws on the methodology established by Zheng et al. (2023),
"Judging LLM-as-a-Judge with MT-Bench and Chatbot Arena," NeurIPS 2023.
